five, four or five years old,

00:02:17.940 --> 00:02:19.640 align:middle line:90%
I did have some--

00:02:19.640 --> 00:02:22.740 align:middle line:84%
I remember dreams and thoughts
that were very metaphysical,

00:02:22.740 --> 00:02:23.540 align:middle line:90%
you could say.

00:02:23.540 --> 00:02:24.320 align:middle line:90%
Basically--

00:02:24.320 --> 00:02:25.120 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Share.

00:02:25.120 --> 00:02:28.360 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: --imagining--
well, just imagining, well,

00:02:28.360 --> 00:02:30.740 align:middle line:84%
you're told about
Heaven as a child.

00:02:30.740 --> 00:02:32.249 align:middle line:84%
And I don't know
what people think.

00:02:32.249 --> 00:02:34.040 align:middle line:84%
Personally, I thought,
well, wait a minute.

00:02:34.040 --> 00:02:35.456 align:middle line:84%
Heaven is a place
where you can go

00:02:35.456 --> 00:02:37.770 align:middle line:84%
and you can do everything
you want, all day, everyday.

00:02:37.770 --> 00:02:38.570 align:middle line:90%
So I'm a child.

00:02:38.570 --> 00:02:41.420 align:middle line:84%
I'm thinking, here, I can go
to Heaven and it's amazing.

00:02:41.420 --> 00:02:43.520 align:middle line:84%
It's light, and
every day you play,

00:02:43.520 --> 00:02:46.340 align:middle line:84%
and you get to play and play,
and play, and play, and play,

00:02:46.340 --> 00:02:47.140 align:middle line:90%
and play.

00:02:47.140 --> 00:02:48.590 align:middle line:84%
And you start to
imagine infinity.

00:02:48.590 --> 00:02:50.960 align:middle line:84%
And you start to delve into
this concept of infinity.

00:02:50.960 --> 00:02:51.760 align:middle line:90%
And wait a minute.

00:02:51.760 --> 00:02:53.810 align:middle line:84%
If you can just do whatever
you want every day,

00:02:53.810 --> 00:02:55.930 align:middle line:90%
that becomes a type of torture.

00:02:55.930 --> 00:02:57.070 align:middle line:90%
It becomes a--

00:02:57.070 --> 00:02:59.300 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's very
astute for a five-year-old.

00:02:59.300 --> 00:03:00.100 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Yeah.

00:03:00.100 --> 00:03:02.277 align:middle line:84%
And this notion
of, wait a minute.

00:03:02.277 --> 00:03:03.860 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if
that's Heaven anymore,

00:03:03.860 --> 00:03:05.750 align:middle line:84%
because you're
getting whatever you

00:03:05.750 --> 00:03:08.180 align:middle line:90%
want all the time, immediately.

00:03:08.180 --> 00:03:11.322 align:middle line:84%
And I think that,
in a sense, I then

00:03:11.322 --> 00:03:13.280 align:middle line:84%
started saying, well,
maybe that's not reality.

00:03:13.280 --> 00:03:15.800 align:middle line:84%
Maybe that Heaven
is not a real one,

00:03:15.800 --> 00:03:18.290 align:middle line:84%
because it becomes
like a torture.

00:03:18.290 --> 00:03:20.970 align:middle line:84%
And then on the other extreme,
if you say that at death,

00:03:20.970 --> 00:03:23.630 align:middle line:84%
there's only darkness
and black night,

00:03:23.630 --> 00:03:25.230 align:middle line:84%
and you just imagined
sort of this--

00:03:25.230 --> 00:03:26.030 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Worms.

00:03:26.030 --> 00:03:26.330 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Well, no.

00:03:26.330 --> 00:03:27.620 align:middle line:90%
Just this tomb of darkness.

00:03:27.620 --> 00:03:27.920 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:03:27.920 --> 00:03:29.020 align:middle line:90%
But like nothing.

00:03:29.020 --> 00:03:29.850 align:middle line:90%
Not even worms.

00:03:29.850 --> 00:03:32.250 align:middle line:90%
Just sensory deprivation.

00:03:32.250 --> 00:03:33.050 align:middle line:90%
Wow.

00:03:33.050 --> 00:03:34.570 align:middle line:90%
That's pretty frightening too.

00:03:34.570 --> 00:03:35.370 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:03:35.370 --> 00:03:37.820 align:middle line:84%
So from there, you start
to delve into these other--

00:03:37.820 --> 00:03:39.950 align:middle line:90%
those are two extremes.

00:03:39.950 --> 00:03:42.350 align:middle line:84%
And you start to delve
into other aspects of what

00:03:42.350 --> 00:03:43.340 align:middle line:90%
actually does happen.

00:03:43.340 --> 00:03:46.779 align:middle line:84%
And then I went with my father
to India at 10 years old,

00:03:46.779 --> 00:03:48.320 align:middle line:84%
and he taught me
about the third eye.

00:03:48.320 --> 00:03:51.495 align:middle line:84%
He taught me about Buddhism
and concepts of reincarnation.

00:03:51.495 --> 00:03:53.870 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well, that actually
probably makes more sense

00:03:53.870 --> 00:03:57.350 align:middle line:84%
to me, the idea that we're
on this soul's journey,

00:03:57.350 --> 00:04:01.070 align:middle line:84%
and each lifetime is lived so
that we can basically acquire

00:04:01.070 --> 00:04:03.110 align:middle line:90%
wisdom and understanding.

00:04:03.110 --> 00:04:07.010 align:middle line:84%
And basically,
there's some teleology

00:04:07.010 --> 00:04:09.430 align:middle line:84%
as far as our journey of
where we're aiming to go,

00:04:09.430 --> 00:04:10.929 align:middle line:84%
and we don't know
how many lifetimes

00:04:10.929 --> 00:04:12.230 align:middle line:90%
it'll take to get there.

00:04:12.230 --> 00:04:14.825 align:middle line:84%
And the lifetimes can
take us beyond this world,

00:04:14.825 --> 00:04:16.190 align:middle line:90%
to other worlds.

00:04:16.190 --> 00:04:19.550 align:middle line:84%
So then you get into this
concept obviously of aliens,

00:04:19.550 --> 00:04:22.940 align:middle line:84%
and you start to read
books like, in my case,

00:04:22.940 --> 00:04:26.460 align:middle line:84%
David Icke and Jim Marrs
and others and saying, OK.

00:04:26.460 --> 00:04:29.832 align:middle line:84%
Maybe there's an alien reality
that existed that actually not

00:04:29.832 --> 00:04:33.170 align:middle line:84%
only seeded mankind,
the Zecharia Sitchin

00:04:33.170 --> 00:04:35.300 align:middle line:84%
interpretation of the
Sumerian accounts, obviously,

00:04:35.300 --> 00:04:36.440 align:middle line:90%
but there are others.

00:04:36.440 --> 00:04:37.850 align:middle line:90%
And they seeded mankind.

00:04:37.850 --> 00:04:39.680 align:middle line:84%
And then if there
are aliens that

00:04:39.680 --> 00:04:42.520 align:middle line:84%
have been here since the past,
maybe they're still here.

00:04:42.520 --> 00:04:44.420 align:middle line:84%
And maybe our future
is an alien future.

00:04:44.420 --> 00:04:48.050 align:middle line:84%
So I would say this has been my
process, basically, of evolving

00:04:48.050 --> 00:04:50.850 align:middle line:90%
in the metaphysical direction.

00:04:50.850 --> 00:04:53.960 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's very organic,
and also, it was very reflective

00:04:53.960 --> 00:04:55.280 align:middle line:90%
for someone that young.

00:04:55.280 --> 00:04:57.710 align:middle line:84%
When did you start tapping
into the work of people

00:04:57.710 --> 00:05:00.080 align:middle line:90%
like David Icke, for example?

00:05:00.080 --> 00:05:03.590 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: Yeah, I mean, I came
about when I was 17, actually.

00:05:03.590 --> 00:05:06.560 align:middle line:84%
I was at one of those
magical bookshops, I think.

00:05:06.560 --> 00:05:09.530 align:middle line:84%
There's a few of them around
in places like LA and New York.

00:05:09.530 --> 00:05:11.450 align:middle line:84%
And so in LA, I went to
one of the bookshops,

00:05:11.450 --> 00:05:13.890 align:middle line:84%
and I was digging through
the conspiracy section.

00:05:13.890 --> 00:05:15.890 align:middle line:84%
And we'll talk about the
other conspiracy angle,

00:05:15.890 --> 00:05:17.780 align:middle line:84%
because obviously, I knew
about conspiracies from--

00:05:17.780 --> 00:05:19.410 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, we're going to
talk about that in just a sec.

00:05:19.410 --> 00:05:21.159 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: Yeah, the
historical perspective.

00:05:21.159 --> 00:05:24.880 align:middle line:84%
But you know, being in a
bookshop and reading conspiracy

00:05:24.880 --> 00:05:27.100 align:middle line:84%
books, and "The Biggest
Secret" popped out to me.

00:05:27.100 --> 00:05:28.475 align:middle line:84%
I think was "The
Biggest Secret."

00:05:28.475 --> 00:05:31.900 align:middle line:84%
And it was just sort of
gigantic in its scope.

00:05:31.900 --> 00:05:34.720 align:middle line:84%
And I've always been
interested about history.

00:05:34.720 --> 00:05:36.580 align:middle line:84%
So to me, it was
like a gateway drug.

00:05:36.580 --> 00:05:38.360 align:middle line:90%
It opened the door to this idea.

00:05:38.360 --> 00:05:39.160 align:middle line:90%
What are Masons?

00:05:39.160 --> 00:05:39.960 align:middle line:90%
What are Templars?

00:05:39.960 --> 00:05:42.340 align:middle line:84%
What is this Hermetic
Gnostic tradition

00:05:42.340 --> 00:05:44.770 align:middle line:84%
that we see in art and
certain depict-- basically,

00:05:44.770 --> 00:05:49.030 align:middle line:84%
certain secret society
portrayals of history

00:05:49.030 --> 00:05:51.520 align:middle line:84%
that is the alternative
path, basically,

00:05:51.520 --> 00:05:53.920 align:middle line:84%
if you look deeper
beneath the surface.

00:05:53.920 --> 00:05:55.474 align:middle line:90%
And then he introduced me to--

00:05:55.474 --> 00:05:56.890 align:middle line:84%
his book introduced
me to Sitchin,

00:05:56.890 --> 00:05:59.950 align:middle line:84%
and I read "The 12th
Planet" and that series.

00:05:59.950 --> 00:06:04.620 align:middle line:84%
So really came through
17, 18, that time period.

00:06:04.620 --> 00:06:08.700 align:middle line:84%
Going off to college, I became
more aware, I would say,

00:06:08.700 --> 00:06:11.160 align:middle line:84%
of these concepts of
multidimensionality.

00:06:11.160 --> 00:06:12.784 align:middle line:84%
But again, I never
experienced it.

00:06:12.784 --> 00:06:14.700 align:middle line:84%
This was all from an
intellectual perspective,

00:06:14.700 --> 00:06:16.680 align:middle line:84%
someone who was trying
to understand the world

00:06:16.680 --> 00:06:19.850 align:middle line:84%
purely as an
intellectual scholar,

00:06:19.850 --> 00:06:21.620 align:middle line:84%
or someone who's going
to-- at that time,

00:06:21.620 --> 00:06:22.560 align:middle line:90%
I was going to Princeton.

00:06:22.560 --> 00:06:23.643 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to study history.

00:06:23.643 --> 00:06:27.615 align:middle line:84%
I was very keen on
scholarship and reading

00:06:27.615 --> 00:06:30.645 align:middle line:84%
and having citations
and sources and not--

00:06:30.645 --> 00:06:32.770 align:middle line:84%
you can speculate and
obviously have fun with that,

00:06:32.770 --> 00:06:34.740 align:middle line:84%
but when it comes to
delivering a paper,

00:06:34.740 --> 00:06:38.100 align:middle line:84%
you have to be balanced and
grounded in what can be proven.

00:06:38.100 --> 00:06:42.110 align:middle line:84%
So that was my journey up
till the post-college era.

00:06:42.110 --> 00:06:44.680 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And did it create
a little bit of a split

00:06:44.680 --> 00:06:46.290 align:middle line:84%
in at least your
desire and where

00:06:46.290 --> 00:06:48.330 align:middle line:84%
you wanted to go in
your mind to be exposed

00:06:48.330 --> 00:06:51.060 align:middle line:84%
to all the conspiracy and
the notion of other worlds,

00:06:51.060 --> 00:06:54.900 align:middle line:84%
ETs and other developing
civilizations here,

00:06:54.900 --> 00:06:58.620 align:middle line:84%
and then have to be incredibly
academic at the same time?

00:06:58.620 --> 00:07:01.887 align:middle line:84%
Did you have fellows that you
could chat with about this?

00:07:01.887 --> 00:07:02.720 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Not really.

00:07:02.720 --> 00:07:04.790 align:middle line:84%
Actually, it was a
lonely time, I would say.

00:07:04.790 --> 00:07:06.702 align:middle line:90%
Actually, it was a hard thing.

00:07:06.702 --> 00:07:08.160 align:middle line:84%
It was a very
isolating experience,

00:07:08.160 --> 00:07:12.360 align:middle line:84%
being in high
school and college.

00:07:12.360 --> 00:07:16.020 align:middle line:84%
Because on one hand,
like you said, I was,

00:07:16.020 --> 00:07:17.790 align:middle line:84%
A, I was interested
by these things

00:07:17.790 --> 00:07:19.410 align:middle line:90%
that were extradimensional.

00:07:19.410 --> 00:07:22.744 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time, I was
still grounded in my studies,

00:07:22.744 --> 00:07:24.910 align:middle line:84%
and I was also-- you know,
it's an internal journey.

00:07:24.910 --> 00:07:26.220 align:middle line:90%
It's a very lonely journey.

00:07:26.220 --> 00:07:27.450 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's like
you have to seal off

00:07:27.450 --> 00:07:28.410 align:middle line:90%
one part from the other.

00:07:28.410 --> 00:07:28.920 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Correct.

00:07:28.920 --> 00:07:31.086 align:middle line:84%
And that's, I think, what
happened, what did happen.

00:07:31.086 --> 00:07:34.230 align:middle line:84%
Because I remember at
13, actually, about 13 I

00:07:34.230 --> 00:07:38.130 align:middle line:84%
was in Vietnam with my father,
and we were going there,

00:07:38.130 --> 00:07:40.350 align:middle line:84%
him as a veteran
of the Vietnam War.

00:07:40.350 --> 00:07:43.090 align:middle line:84%
He'd been there before many
times, but he took me there.

00:07:43.090 --> 00:07:46.530 align:middle line:84%
And we basically relived
this very beautiful journey

00:07:46.530 --> 00:07:51.930 align:middle line:84%
through from the tunnels of Cu
Chi, Saigon, Hanoi, Da Nang,

00:07:51.930 --> 00:07:53.590 align:middle line:90%
all these different places.

00:07:53.590 --> 00:07:56.460 align:middle line:84%
And he was haunted by it, but
he was exploring it with me

00:07:56.460 --> 00:07:58.084 align:middle line:90%
and sharing the country with me.

00:07:58.084 --> 00:07:59.500 align:middle line:84%
And when we were
there and looking

00:07:59.500 --> 00:08:00.900 align:middle line:84%
at the museum and
the war museum,

00:08:00.900 --> 00:08:02.941 align:middle line:84%
and reflecting on the
millions of Vietnamese that

00:08:02.941 --> 00:08:05.820 align:middle line:84%
had been killed and
traumatized by this war,

00:08:05.820 --> 00:08:08.640 align:middle line:84%
I started downloading
really interesting imagery

00:08:08.640 --> 00:08:11.250 align:middle line:90%
of a new world order, basically.

00:08:11.250 --> 00:08:12.944 align:middle line:84%
I had no idea what
the concept was.

00:08:12.944 --> 00:08:14.610 align:middle line:84%
I don't even know if
I'd heard the term.

00:08:14.610 --> 00:08:18.300 align:middle line:84%
But essentially, I
was seeing this map--

00:08:18.300 --> 00:08:20.500 align:middle line:84%
sorry, the flag of the
United States transforming,

00:08:20.500 --> 00:08:23.175 align:middle line:84%
and basically, a globe
was replacing the stars.

00:08:23.175 --> 00:08:25.140 align:middle line:84%
It was basically
saying, there's a story

00:08:25.140 --> 00:08:27.390 align:middle line:84%
being downloaded about
how the world was going

00:08:27.390 --> 00:08:29.370 align:middle line:90%
to become organized under one--

00:08:29.370 --> 00:08:31.800 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That certainly
was where it was fomented.

00:08:31.800 --> 00:08:33.299 align:middle line:84%
Vietnam War was a
big part of that.

00:08:33.299 --> 00:08:33.840 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Perhaps.

00:08:33.840 --> 00:08:35.669 align:middle line:84%
I mean, but it was weird to
download this information

00:08:35.669 --> 00:08:37.679 align:middle line:84%
at 13 about global
governance, and the idea

00:08:37.679 --> 00:08:40.169 align:middle line:84%
that Lucifer or some
kind of satanic figure

00:08:40.169 --> 00:08:42.100 align:middle line:84%
was really behind
it, and they were

00:08:42.100 --> 00:08:45.570 align:middle line:84%
going to use the pretense
of de-disarming everyone,

00:08:45.570 --> 00:08:48.780 align:middle line:84%
bringing everyone--
de-nuclearization as a process,

00:08:48.780 --> 00:08:49.640 align:middle line:90%
basically.

00:08:49.640 --> 00:08:52.769 align:middle line:84%
It's ultimately put the
power into one hand, which

00:08:52.769 --> 00:08:54.060 align:middle line:90%
is ultimately the devil's hand.

00:08:54.060 --> 00:08:56.700 align:middle line:84%
And the devil is going to use
it to destroy America first,

00:08:56.700 --> 00:08:57.819 align:middle line:90%
and then the whole planet.

00:08:57.819 --> 00:09:00.360 align:middle line:84%
And this was just a story that
downloaded to me at that time.

00:09:00.360 --> 00:09:01.662 align:middle line:90%
It was very visual.

00:09:01.662 --> 00:09:02.620 align:middle line:90%
I wrote a script of it.

00:09:02.620 --> 00:09:05.057 align:middle line:84%
But it was weird, because I
had not heard this concept--

00:09:05.057 --> 00:09:07.140 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And how old were
you again at that time?

00:09:07.140 --> 00:09:07.545 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: 13.

00:09:07.545 --> 00:09:07.950 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: 13.

00:09:07.950 --> 00:09:08.570 align:middle line:90%
Right, yeah.

00:09:08.570 --> 00:09:09.240 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Yeah.

00:09:09.240 --> 00:09:10.040 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:09:10.040 --> 00:09:12.180 align:middle line:84%
So your mind was already
beginning to put pieces

00:09:12.180 --> 00:09:13.560 align:middle line:90%
together in original ways.

00:09:13.560 --> 00:09:16.036 align:middle line:84%
Were you able to always
talk with your-- well, both

00:09:16.036 --> 00:09:17.910 align:middle line:84%
your mother and father,
were you able to talk

00:09:17.910 --> 00:09:19.560 align:middle line:84%
over these various
concepts with them?

00:09:19.560 --> 00:09:24.450 align:middle line:84%
Were they open to all of the
things that you were exploring?

00:09:24.450 --> 00:09:28.860 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: I mean, you know,
my father is someone who is

00:09:28.860 --> 00:09:30.180 align:middle line:90%
actually very--

00:09:30.180 --> 00:09:32.070 align:middle line:84%
I would say rational
and materialistic

00:09:32.070 --> 00:09:34.480 align:middle line:84%
in terms of his
thinking about reality.

00:09:34.480 --> 00:09:36.960 align:middle line:84%
He's someone who takes
the Buddhist perception.

00:09:36.960 --> 00:09:40.390 align:middle line:84%
And all of reality is
the mind, basically.

00:09:40.390 --> 00:09:43.020 align:middle line:84%
So if you believe
in ghosts, if you

00:09:43.020 --> 00:09:46.990 align:middle line:84%
believe in gods and devils and
all this, it's ultimately--

00:09:46.990 --> 00:09:50.430 align:middle line:84%
it's only as true as you
believe it to be, right?

00:09:50.430 --> 00:09:52.440 align:middle line:90%
He would take that perception.

00:09:52.440 --> 00:09:55.110 align:middle line:84%
And so when I wrote this
script, for example,

00:09:55.110 --> 00:09:58.500 align:middle line:84%
he couldn't understand at all
the concept of the devil figure

00:09:58.500 --> 00:10:03.480 align:middle line:84%
being a real character and
all these supernatural forces

00:10:03.480 --> 00:10:07.110 align:middle line:84%
that, to me, actually
make more sense

00:10:07.110 --> 00:10:08.940 align:middle line:90%
having lived through it later.

00:10:08.940 --> 00:10:11.160 align:middle line:84%
But at the time, it was
literally just an imagination

00:10:11.160 --> 00:10:12.570 align:middle line:90%
of a kid who's--

00:10:12.570 --> 00:10:15.450 align:middle line:84%
frankly, I've always been
interested in sword and sandal

00:10:15.450 --> 00:10:17.857 align:middle line:84%
fantasies, sci-fi, I
think, more than him.

00:10:17.857 --> 00:10:19.440 align:middle line:84%
And it reflects in
his work, you know?

00:10:19.440 --> 00:10:21.300 align:middle line:84%
He's someone who's very
much a rationalist.

00:10:21.300 --> 00:10:23.910 align:middle line:84%
If you look at his project,
they're always biographies.

00:10:23.910 --> 00:10:25.770 align:middle line:84%
They're always rooted
in the real world.

00:10:25.770 --> 00:10:29.740 align:middle line:84%
"The Doors" may be the
most esoteric of the pieces

00:10:29.740 --> 00:10:32.370 align:middle line:84%
where they have a bit of
the ghosts of the Indians

00:10:32.370 --> 00:10:34.660 align:middle line:90%
intruding into it.

00:10:34.660 --> 00:10:37.892 align:middle line:84%
But again, he would say, it's
all the mind, the mindscape.

00:10:37.892 --> 00:10:40.350 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But didn't you say
when you were in India that he

00:10:40.350 --> 00:10:43.540 align:middle line:84%
was turning you on to these
other higher concepts,

00:10:43.540 --> 00:10:44.740 align:middle line:90%
including reincarnation?

00:10:44.740 --> 00:10:45.990 align:middle line:90%
Where does that work with him?

00:10:45.990 --> 00:10:46.920 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: Because
it's just the mind.

00:10:46.920 --> 00:10:49.176 align:middle line:84%
It's the mind that carries
over from body to body.

00:10:49.176 --> 00:10:49.976 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I see.

00:10:49.976 --> 00:10:51.990 align:middle line:84%
So nothing empirical
other than just

00:10:51.990 --> 00:10:53.980 align:middle line:84%
whatever the thought
is able to create.

00:10:53.980 --> 00:10:54.780 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Right.

00:10:54.780 --> 00:10:57.780 align:middle line:84%
Precisely Nothing in
terms of, I would say,

00:10:57.780 --> 00:11:02.029 align:middle line:84%
the extraterrestrial,
esoteric domain.

00:11:02.029 --> 00:11:03.570 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's
where he would stop.

00:11:03.570 --> 00:11:03.900 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Right.

00:11:03.900 --> 00:11:05.524 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But he
obviously is intrigued

00:11:05.524 --> 00:11:07.280 align:middle line:84%
with alternative
versions, concepts.

00:11:07.280 --> 00:11:11.040 align:middle line:84%
I mean, he does brilliant work
as bringing up the conspiracies

00:11:11.040 --> 00:11:12.480 align:middle line:90%
in the rational world.

00:11:12.480 --> 00:11:14.160 align:middle line:90%
But you're taking that further.

00:11:14.160 --> 00:11:16.185 align:middle line:90%
And what about your mother?

00:11:16.185 --> 00:11:17.590 align:middle line:90%
How is she wired in terms of--

00:11:17.590 --> 00:11:19.580 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: She's someone
who believes in angels.

00:11:19.580 --> 00:11:24.444 align:middle line:84%
She believes very much
in these principles.

00:11:24.444 --> 00:11:25.860 align:middle line:84%
On the other hand,
you know, she's

00:11:25.860 --> 00:11:27.720 align:middle line:84%
not someone who
practices religion.

00:11:27.720 --> 00:11:30.060 align:middle line:90%
You know, she was born Catholic.

00:11:30.060 --> 00:11:33.610 align:middle line:90%
Really more of a Protestant.

00:11:33.610 --> 00:11:35.640 align:middle line:84%
But then, I mean,
basically lapsed

00:11:35.640 --> 00:11:37.380 align:middle line:84%
because the Catholic
church, as we

00:11:37.380 --> 00:11:39.420 align:middle line:84%
know, the way that
they'd school you,

00:11:39.420 --> 00:11:41.734 align:middle line:84%
the nurses would
whip them, basically.

00:11:41.734 --> 00:11:43.400 align:middle line:84%
They'd crack their
knuckles with rulers.

00:11:43.400 --> 00:11:46.172 align:middle line:90%
They were very abysmally cruel.

00:11:46.172 --> 00:11:47.880 align:middle line:84%
So she ran away from
the Catholic church,

00:11:47.880 --> 00:11:49.790 align:middle line:90%
went to the Protestant side.

00:11:49.790 --> 00:11:52.544 align:middle line:84%
But ultimately, she took
me to the Self-Realization

00:11:52.544 --> 00:11:54.210 align:middle line:84%
Fellowship, you know,
Yogananda's thing.

00:11:54.210 --> 00:11:54.530 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: There you go.

00:11:54.530 --> 00:11:54.900 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:11:54.900 --> 00:11:56.816 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: And that was a
really important thing

00:11:56.816 --> 00:11:59.730 align:middle line:84%
in my upbringing, was
actually to worship and study

00:11:59.730 --> 00:12:01.174 align:middle line:90%
from all texts.

00:12:01.174 --> 00:12:02.590 align:middle line:84%
You know, that was
the concept was

00:12:02.590 --> 00:12:04.530 align:middle line:84%
you go to the
Self-Realization Fellowship

00:12:04.530 --> 00:12:06.480 align:middle line:84%
and you would hear a
sermon, and it could

00:12:06.480 --> 00:12:08.670 align:middle line:90%
be quoting from the Quran.

00:12:08.670 --> 00:12:09.960 align:middle line:90%
It could be from The Vedas.

00:12:09.960 --> 00:12:12.810 align:middle line:84%
It could be from
Buddhist teachings,

00:12:12.810 --> 00:12:15.660 align:middle line:84%
it could be Daoist,
Christian, Jewish.

00:12:15.660 --> 00:12:19.170 align:middle line:84%
You basically
honored the one god,

00:12:19.170 --> 00:12:21.900 align:middle line:84%
which all the fates
are basically derived

00:12:21.900 --> 00:12:24.090 align:middle line:90%
from a one-source concept.

00:12:24.090 --> 00:12:26.430 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, and now,
if you go from there,

00:12:26.430 --> 00:12:29.400 align:middle line:84%
it doesn't really matter which
of those traditions you follow.

00:12:29.400 --> 00:12:33.240 align:middle line:84%
They'll all go into the
notion of dark realms.

00:12:33.240 --> 00:12:36.030 align:middle line:84%
Humans interfacing with the
great challenge of dark realms.

00:12:36.030 --> 00:12:39.810 align:middle line:84%
And that gets us to the
area of multidimensionality,

00:12:39.810 --> 00:12:42.750 align:middle line:84%
and this feeling
that you've always

00:12:42.750 --> 00:12:44.550 align:middle line:84%
had that there's
something watching,

00:12:44.550 --> 00:12:46.470 align:middle line:84%
and maybe perhaps
more than watching.

00:12:46.470 --> 00:12:49.950 align:middle line:84%
So I think this would be a
good time to get into that.

00:12:49.950 --> 00:12:51.750 align:middle line:84%
In your perception,
having thought

00:12:51.750 --> 00:12:53.730 align:middle line:84%
this over most of your
lifetime, what do you

00:12:53.730 --> 00:12:57.030 align:middle line:84%
think it is that's
interfacing with humanity

00:12:57.030 --> 00:12:59.520 align:middle line:90%
or watching or interfering?

00:12:59.520 --> 00:13:02.280 align:middle line:84%
And what do you feel
the purpose of it is?

00:13:02.280 --> 00:13:03.989 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Hmm.

00:13:03.989 --> 00:13:05.030 align:middle line:90%
Well, it depends if I'm--

00:13:05.030 --> 00:13:05.700 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Take your time.

00:13:05.700 --> 00:13:07.533 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: --in a good
mood or in a dark mood.

00:13:07.533 --> 00:13:08.502 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:13:08.502 --> 00:13:08.980 align:middle line:90%


00:13:08.980 --> 00:13:09.780 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:13:09.780 --> 00:13:11.070 align:middle line:90%
Let me set it up this way.

00:13:11.070 --> 00:13:14.460 align:middle line:84%
It should be known that
all those traditions also

00:13:14.460 --> 00:13:17.970 align:middle line:84%
have the higher realms
intersecting with this plane

00:13:17.970 --> 00:13:19.170 align:middle line:90%
that human beings live on.

00:13:19.170 --> 00:13:20.730 align:middle line:84%
We have the lower
and the higher.

00:13:20.730 --> 00:13:21.330 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Precisely.

00:13:21.330 --> 00:13:22.130 align:middle line:90%
Precisely.

00:13:22.130 --> 00:13:25.620 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there is a
truth to the idea

00:13:25.620 --> 00:13:27.080 align:middle line:90%
that it's about perception.

00:13:27.080 --> 00:13:29.302 align:middle line:84%
How do we want to
perceive things?

00:13:29.302 --> 00:13:32.580 align:middle line:84%
I've had initiation
journeys where I recognized

00:13:32.580 --> 00:13:35.040 align:middle line:84%
the devils were actually
just the angels' wings,

00:13:35.040 --> 00:13:37.770 align:middle line:84%
and basically they were
wearing masks to scare people,

00:13:37.770 --> 00:13:40.410 align:middle line:84%
essentially, to
test you, to see,

00:13:40.410 --> 00:13:44.460 align:middle line:84%
are you courageous enough to
face those demons, a darkness,

00:13:44.460 --> 00:13:45.770 align:middle line:90%
and not be afraid?

00:13:45.770 --> 00:13:48.330 align:middle line:84%
If you are afraid, they
have power over you.

00:13:48.330 --> 00:13:50.754 align:middle line:84%
They will get you into
all kinds of traps.

00:13:50.754 --> 00:13:51.920 align:middle line:90%
And that's the way I see it.

00:13:51.920 --> 00:13:55.250 align:middle line:84%
I see it like a soul journey,
where basically, your soul

00:13:55.250 --> 00:13:56.490 align:middle line:90%
is being tested.

00:13:56.490 --> 00:13:57.840 align:middle line:90%
Where does it stand?

00:13:57.840 --> 00:14:02.370 align:middle line:84%
Does it want to basically bow
down to the rulers, the kings,

00:14:02.370 --> 00:14:04.080 align:middle line:90%
the people with money that--

00:14:04.080 --> 00:14:05.942 align:middle line:90%
the illusion of power?

00:14:05.942 --> 00:14:07.650 align:middle line:84%
Those demons, do you
want to bow to them?

00:14:07.650 --> 00:14:09.120 align:middle line:84%
Do you want to make
deals with them

00:14:09.120 --> 00:14:11.790 align:middle line:84%
to increase your own power
within this physical realm?

00:14:11.790 --> 00:14:13.900 align:middle line:84%
Because we know
it's all transitory.

00:14:13.900 --> 00:14:17.930 align:middle line:84%
It's all illusion in that
sense that it won't last.

00:14:17.930 --> 00:14:21.900 align:middle line:84%
So is it really worth
trading our soul energy,

00:14:21.900 --> 00:14:24.120 align:middle line:84%
that initial light,
spark that comes

00:14:24.120 --> 00:14:26.370 align:middle line:84%
from the primordial
source, is it worth

00:14:26.370 --> 00:14:30.390 align:middle line:84%
trading this goal that is
within us already innately

00:14:30.390 --> 00:14:34.820 align:middle line:84%
for some fool's gold that
is offered along the way?

00:14:34.820 --> 00:14:37.110 align:middle line:84%
And so many people are
willing to basically trade

00:14:37.110 --> 00:14:39.719 align:middle line:84%
what is most valuable, what is
the thing that they actually

00:14:39.719 --> 00:14:41.760 align:middle line:84%
want most, which is to
actually return to source,

00:14:41.760 --> 00:14:44.370 align:middle line:84%
which is actually to
shed light and commune

00:14:44.370 --> 00:14:47.960 align:middle line:84%
with other beings in a pure
sense, in a loving sense.

00:14:47.960 --> 00:14:50.520 align:middle line:84%
And they're willing to trade
that for a temporary moment

00:14:50.520 --> 00:14:53.990 align:middle line:90%
of satisfaction, comfort.

00:14:53.990 --> 00:14:57.360 align:middle line:84%
And obviously, it's a difficult,
tremendously difficult journey.

00:14:57.360 --> 00:14:59.010 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you can't
answer for everyone

00:14:59.010 --> 00:15:01.200 align:middle line:84%
and tell them, you know,
what they need to do,

00:15:01.200 --> 00:15:02.980 align:middle line:84%
because ultimately,
it's their own course.

00:15:02.980 --> 00:15:06.486 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes you have to go through
the hells to experience that.

00:15:06.486 --> 00:15:07.860 align:middle line:84%
That's what you
were meant to do.

00:15:07.860 --> 00:15:13.440 align:middle line:84%
So I really can't condemn
people for being, to my mind,

00:15:13.440 --> 00:15:15.720 align:middle line:90%
wicked or cruel or mean or evil.

00:15:15.720 --> 00:15:17.370 align:middle line:90%
It's their own path.

00:15:17.370 --> 00:15:20.130 align:middle line:84%
And all I can do is recognize
maybe where they went wrong

00:15:20.130 --> 00:15:23.220 align:middle line:84%
and where I would want
to basically not follow

00:15:23.220 --> 00:15:25.000 align:middle line:90%
that same trajectory.

00:15:25.000 --> 00:15:30.630 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So on a larger level,
do you believe that the darker

00:15:30.630 --> 00:15:31.440 align:middle line:90%
realms--

00:15:31.440 --> 00:15:33.870 align:middle line:84%
we would call them darker
realms-- the challenging realms

00:15:33.870 --> 00:15:37.260 align:middle line:84%
and the lighter realms or
those that choose to or assist

00:15:37.260 --> 00:15:40.650 align:middle line:84%
in upliftment are
of the same source,

00:15:40.650 --> 00:15:44.310 align:middle line:84%
and are simply playing
out their own roles

00:15:44.310 --> 00:15:48.210 align:middle line:84%
here in terms of their
interface with humanity?

00:15:48.210 --> 00:15:49.950 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Yes, of course.

00:15:49.950 --> 00:15:56.670 align:middle line:84%
We know that if there is a
primordial light that casts out

00:15:56.670 --> 00:16:01.010 align:middle line:84%
and then basically continues to
shine throughout the universe,

00:16:01.010 --> 00:16:04.150 align:middle line:84%
but then it also slows
into material forms, right?

00:16:04.150 --> 00:16:08.090 align:middle line:84%
Matter itself is a different
expression of that same energy.

00:16:08.090 --> 00:16:09.350 align:middle line:90%
And it's slowed down energy.

00:16:09.350 --> 00:16:13.840 align:middle line:84%
It's basically-- it's
light in slow motion.

00:16:13.840 --> 00:16:18.130 align:middle line:84%
And when that matter
forms, it casts the shadow.

00:16:18.130 --> 00:16:21.520 align:middle line:84%
So the shadow is a necessary
consequence of the light,

00:16:21.520 --> 00:16:23.260 align:middle line:84%
like the Zorastrians
would put it, right?

00:16:23.260 --> 00:16:25.600 align:middle line:84%
There's always going to
be the dark and the light,

00:16:25.600 --> 00:16:29.350 align:middle line:84%
and that you have to respect
and honor that, and know,

00:16:29.350 --> 00:16:32.830 align:middle line:84%
I would say, even in Kabbalah
and other spiritual traditions

00:16:32.830 --> 00:16:36.959 align:middle line:84%
to understand that there
is always a time for war,

00:16:36.959 --> 00:16:38.000 align:middle line:90%
there's a time for peace.

00:16:38.000 --> 00:16:40.750 align:middle line:84%
There's a time to be severe,
there's a time to be lenient.

00:16:40.750 --> 00:16:43.060 align:middle line:84%
We have to recognize
this balance.

00:16:43.060 --> 00:16:45.340 align:middle line:84%
And it's a difficult
thing, right?

00:16:45.340 --> 00:16:48.220 align:middle line:84%
Because not everybody can
get to that place of wisdom,

00:16:48.220 --> 00:16:51.490 align:middle line:84%
that place of a King Solomon,
to understand essentially

00:16:51.490 --> 00:16:56.620 align:middle line:84%
how to be just, how to rule,
how to basically wield the left

00:16:56.620 --> 00:16:58.300 align:middle line:90%
with the right in harmony.

00:16:58.300 --> 00:17:01.660 align:middle line:84%
Most people, I would say, are
struggling with that concept

00:17:01.660 --> 00:17:03.220 align:middle line:90%
throughout their lives.

00:17:03.220 --> 00:17:05.046 align:middle line:84%
So yes, to answer
the question, is

00:17:05.046 --> 00:17:06.670 align:middle line:84%
it "all a stage" like
Shakespeare said?

00:17:06.670 --> 00:17:07.470 align:middle line:90%
I believe so.

00:17:07.470 --> 00:17:09.940 align:middle line:84%
I think it's all a
game, and each one of us

00:17:09.940 --> 00:17:13.220 align:middle line:84%
playing the role that resonates
with our soul and, again,

00:17:13.220 --> 00:17:14.020 align:middle line:90%
our journey.

00:17:14.020 --> 00:17:15.436 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, I
agree with that.

00:17:15.436 --> 00:17:18.970 align:middle line:84%
I mean, to not demonize
the lower realms,

00:17:18.970 --> 00:17:20.900 align:middle line:90%
because they are forming--

00:17:20.900 --> 00:17:24.550 align:middle line:84%
they're performing their own
function for their own growth.

